# Known-good command names for the reject-obfuscated-commands hook.
# One name per line; blank lines and #-comments are ignored.
# Path-qualified invocations (/usr/bin/git, ./scripts/x, <hooks-path>/pre-commit)
# are matched by basename. A command that is not on this list (and not on
# command-blocklist, which wins) is rejected outright — extend this file
# when a new tool is legitimately required, rather than changing hook logic.
